name: Thanksgiving Quesadilla
author: Gevans
summary: Turkey and cranberry quesadillas. You can use any cheese in place of the Cheddar cheese, if desired. To flip the quesadilla, place a plate over the skillet and turn the skillet over; slide quesadilla back into skillet!
ingredients: ¼ pound shredded cooked turkey meat
½  jalapeno pepper, seeded and minced
2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro, or to taste
directions: Heat a skillet over medium heat
Place 1 tortilla in the skillet and top with 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese, turkey, cranberry sauce, jalapeno pepper, green onion, and remaining Cheddar cheese, respectively
Place remaining tortilla over the top
Cook until tortilla is golden brown and cheese is melted, 2 to 4 minutes per side
